Height is an issue but makes up for it with hops and technique.  Great router to the sidelines.  Poor zone guy.  Slow recognition, poor timing.  Can get chucked off the line when the run goes to his side, had trouble in the BC game with that.  Poor technique on play break downs, gets in front of the receiver.  Can get driven off a route if he lands on the outside hip.

Mobile, shifty QB in a Lane Kiffin offense.  Shotgun, make a decision, throw it.  Great zip and accuracy, makes some effortless throws.  Big guy and mobile, doesn't get sacked too easily, can make plays with his feet.  Saavy after the snap due to designed QB runs, picked up some experience reading LOS's and making good shovel passes.  Generally good decision maker, finds open guys and hits them.  Tests the margins, bailed out by his receivers a lot but still puts them in a position to succeed.  Pretty tough runner, not the biggest guy in the world but uses his size to punish DBs.  Long, looping throw with a bit of a htich in it.  Decent enough footwork but seems to lose some consistency, specifically on timing throws across the middle.  Much better at leading a receiver vertically than horizontally.  Calm in the face of pressure but not smart, just dumps off.  Definitely seems to look at the LOS before looking down field, antsy in the pocket.  Just ducks into sacks if they're head on, doesn't hang tough to make the throw.  Running style is very physical and punishing.  Relies on improvisation and roll outs to find open lanes and seems to be more comfortable doing that than passing in the pocket.  Doesn't really seem to play with anticipation, throws to open guys instead of leading them open

Short area quickness guy.  Runs solid routes and just gets open over and over.  Great contested catcher for his size.  Short but fights hard to make the catch.  Really smart.  Slow as hell, had a terrible 40 at his pro day.  Tiny catch radius, limited to having the ball put on him even though he tries on passes outside his radius.  Can't really block even though he tries.

Mobile, fluid LT.  Just flows off the snap and looks effortless getting into gaps.  Gets to the second level fast.  Wide, hugging technique in pass pro.  Gets his hands on the outside shoulder and creates length.  Great footwork.  Built for zone blocking.  Keeps his head on a swivel and picks up second blocks.  Seems strong enough, but also lower level of play.  Seems to overset to the inside on run blocks and loses his gap assignment for seal offs.  This review has limited tape and is mostly based on highlights.  Hard to find negative plays.

Tweening right tackle.  Only played there and has the length for it but looks and plays like a guard.  Nice lateraly footwork.  Kicks out well, can move in space.  Decent puller.  Long arms with a lean technique for engagement.  Functionally strong with decent ability to move defenders.  Not going to floor someone in a drive block but they will move.  Decent hand placement, attacks elbows well and contains.  Good anchor, blocks bull rushes well and can take on more impactful rushes.  Plodder getting to the corner in pass protection.  Relies more on length and going parallel to the sideline than quickness.  Not that great against more violent rushers.  Loses his hand placement over time and lets rushers get in his space.  Should really kick inside but not exactly a road grader or the best pass blocker, caught in flux.

Solid pass blocker.  Fights well, stands up bull rushes.  Decently strong, wins more on leverage.  Good footwork, keeps his feet moving under him, doesn't get pancaked easily despite lighter frame.  Moves around in the pocket on help blocks.  Active.  Decent hands.  Lands his initial punch well enough.  Big enough to make a difference in the run game.  Generates decent enough push on his shoves.  Raw.  Looks panicked if he doesn't have a block right in front of him.  Doesn't deal with more violent NTs well.  Patient to a fault, kind of lets guys inside his pads.  More of a zone blocker than man.  Scheme limited until he puts on more muscle mass.

Rotational gap shooter.  Used just to explode into someone and create chaos.  Doesn't play a lot but destroys when he does.  Pure athleticism.  Extremely polished technically for someone with no experience.  Great hand placement, chains moves together, gets into the backfield fast.  Huge power for a small package.  Pops people.  Terrible tackler.  Gets hurt all the time.  Don't use him against the run.  Can't do it.  Elite third down rusher, not an every snap guy for a reason.

Energetic box safety.  Plays hard, always around the ball.  Great trigger.  Undersized but hits hard and has really good wrap up.  Tested slow as hell at the combine but plays way faster in game.  Decently smart, diagnoses routes and running lanes well.  Great at the LOS for someone his size.  Patient and finds the lane.  Fast but limited top end speed.  More of a zone guy than anything else, possibly nickle corner.  Old as hell, was a special teamer for four years.  Just ok size, not small just not really going to thump people at the next level.

Tall RT.  Smooth pass protector.  Very nice kick step for a tall tackle.  Moves fluidly.  Good plant foot and strong anchor on the corner.  Shorter arms but uses them well, strikes to the chest plate and maintains throughout the play.  Good mover in space.  Run blocks well out in screens and pulling, finds second blocks.  Decent lean and balance in run blocking in general.  Just not very strong.  Anchor is there but can get absolutely flattened.  Limited arm length causes him to play without bend in pass pro.  Hand fighting is just okay against more violent pass rushers.  Doesn't seem to move anyone on help blocks or combo blocks.  Already 25, missed whole draft process due to injury.

Shifty one cut back.  Decisive and explosive at the line.  Makes a cut and goes.  Quick feet, good short area quickness.  Decent vision, does get caught behind the line but generally good at finding the correct lane, not afraid to bounce it to the outside.  Efficient and no nonense when running, just goes forward.  Good stiff arm, decent contact balance when taken up low by defenders.  Smaller but good pop.  Can get extra yards and fall forward.  Puts his nose into pass blocking even if he's not going to floor anyone.  Plus receiver out of the backfield.  Hold your breath when he pass blocks he might die.  Pretends he's Ashton Jeanty with his presnap standing.  Balance is kind of poor against higher tackles and he's toppled easily.  Dances sometimes behind the line, only average cut back ability.  Feet stop churning when he gets hands on him.  Kind of small and not that strong despite weight, relies more on leverage than plowing anyone over.

Former Bama guy, went to OSU and played way better until he got hurt.  Taller center, good lower body.  Gets to the second level fast and lands big blocks.  Smart, good at identifying blitzes, help blocks and combo blocks well.  Decent lateral agility and can get up the B gap or pull.  Pretty good run blocker.  Gets hands in position well and fights hard.  Footwork lets him get into position fast.  Lighter but good motor.  Constantly tries.  Plays bolt upright and has no knee bend.  Just goes nose down and blocks on runs.  Much more intelligent in pass protection.  T-rex arms.  Achiles tear is concerning and could sap the diversity of his lateral movement game.

Everything you want on the line except size.  Tiny but plays nasty.  Hits hard and fights relentlessly in the wash.  Has a weird knack for guessing playside runs and usually first at the point of attack.  Absurd amount of tackles for college.  Seems really smart but not that great in coverage.  Downhill guy only.  Not going to wow anyone with speed or athleticism.  Relies a lot on play intelligence over power, not sure where you play him.

Coverage guy.  Smart player, recognizes routes well and picks them up with anticipation rather than just high energy.  Pretty decent run defender, uses his size and breaks down well.  Decently fast with a good trigger.  Can do single high duties.  Stiff as hell.  Skipped the agility drills at the combine for a reason.  Loses guys out of breaks because of his hips.

Track star Alabama transfer.  Seems way faster in game than his score at the combine.  Pure burner, lined up everywhere and ran go routes.  Pretty decent route runner, doesn't just rely on speed.  Regularly bailed Ewers out on intermediate routes.  Pretty good hands and tracking ability.  Thin and no muscle.  Chucked easily.  Didn't really produce despite having a QB made to hit him deep.  Speed is elite but he doesn't really hide his go routes so safeties rotate in time.

Tall grad transfer from WKU.  Quick and fast receiving threat.  Good hands, good at finding spots in the zone.  Pretty nice after the catch, gets downfield quick and his hard to bring down.  Good balance and body control, adjusts well to passes, tracks the ball well.  Decent blocker in space.  Not really an in line blocker unless doing chip help.  Old already.  Not really a contested catch guy but creates enough separation to not worry about it too much.  Style of running might not break that many tackles at the next level.

Mountain RT converted to LT.  Tall with long arms.  Supremely powerful.  Can move anyone in college football in the run game.  Bends completely at his waist but has to due to height.  Good anchor, sets feet wide and doesn't let smaller guys just get under him.  Gives up a lot of space in pass protection but doesn't get beat too often on pure bull rushes.  Long arms are a bit slow but ratchet after the block and move guys.  Surprisingly mobile with decent explosion.  Patient, doesn't over commit.  Hard worker and sticks throughout the play.  Terrible hand placement and can get took on spin moves.  Can't recover.  A bit too patient at times and lets guys get inside his chest.  Wears down a bit as the game goes on and isn't as devastating in the run game.  Pads he plays in are too high and look ridiculous.  24 already.

Versatile OL, mostly at guard, swapped to RG when Garret Dellinger got healthy and stayed there for two years.  Really good pass protector, wide stance, good length.  Anchors well against bull rushes.  Pretty smart, reads pass rushing intent before engaging.  Fights pretty well, keeps his feet and doesn't get wrenched.  Gets moved a bit but generally big enough to be an obstacle.  Decent run blocker when he gets push, has the strength to pop and keeps feet moving.  Okay on shorter pulls.  Can't move side to side.  Not a great help blocker, takes too long to get there.  Turns like a bus.  Not a second level blocker.  Tries but is too slow on processing more complex blitzes.  Blocks bolt upright.

Former LG turned LT turned LG.  Great anchor.  Takes strong bull rushes and doesn't move.  Displayed it well at the Senior Bowl.  Good hands.  Strikes well but intelligent placement with more nuance for shiftier rushers.  Can get violent and nasty in run blocking.  Big shover, pops defenders and gets them off balance while creating seal blocks.  Poor bend.  Hurt all the time.  Slow feet, slow hips.  Played LT but not really suited for it.  Can get stacked and ripped due to bend issues.  Some issues blocking may be due to the QB behind him than his fault.

Smaller of the two hard hitting Penn State safeties.  Faster so he played single high most of the time when they went into that formation.  Smart player, reads the field well, diagnoses well in the run game.  Sound tackler and pretty hard hitter.  Great special teamer.  Great in zone coverage.  Keeps his head on a swivel and picks up guys fast.  Kind of just average size, more of a help guy in run support than point of attack.  Not sure if asked to just attack the line or misses running lanes.  Not really a man cover guy, is tall but gets jumped over.
